<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2448] Scanner threads are interrupted without acquiring lock properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2448</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a few places where scanner threads are interrupted with .interrupt() instead of .interruptIfAlive(). This means that if they&apos;re in the midst of the checkFileSystem operation, it&apos;ll end up catching the interruption there, determine that the filesystem is down, and shut down the whole server. Other nasties can also result.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12462075">HBASE-2448</key>
            <summary>Scanner threads are interrupted without acquiring lock properly</summary>
